column2:
prep. See Amidst.
prep. In the midst or middle of; surrounded or encompassed by;
   among.

v. to cause to separate and go in different directions
v. move away from each other; 
v. separate (light) into spectral rays

n. The state or quality of being reluctant; repugnance;
   aversion of mind; unwillingness; -- often followed by an infinitive, or
   by to and a noun, formerly sometimes by against.
